{"title":"Olympic BMX Racing and BMX Freestyle: How to watch BMX at the Olympics","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/19/olympic-bmx-racing-and-bmx-freestyle-how-to-watch-bmx-at-the-olympics/","date":1626708883000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>BMX isn’t new to the Olympics, but a new discipline will be making its debut this summer at the Tokyo Olympics 2021 — BMX Freestyle.</p><p>Now, I’m sure you’re wondering a whole bunch about how this specific realm of cycling works and hows it is judged. You’re not alone; many spandex and even the baggie crowd have limited BMX experience. That’s why we’re going to layout how BMX cycling at the Olympics works, how it’s judged, and how to watch it.</p><figure id=\"attachment_265138\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-265138\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" alt=\"Rio de Janeiro-Brazil, August 11, 2016- BMX cycling competition during the 2016 Olympic Games\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.c