s://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13132441/Rio-Olympics-BMX-racing-Editorial-credit-A-RICARDO-Shutterstock-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-265138\">A.RICARDO / Shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure><h2>What is it — Olympic BMX Racing</h2><p>These aren’t the BMX bike that you see around your neighborhood and at your local trails — these are bikes that are built to jump but also roll fast and smooth on flowing BMX tracks. Bicycle Motocross (BMX) is raced on dirt or asphalt tracks with similar features on each — different elements ranging from rollers to jumps to berms.</p><p>Riders line up at the starting gate, and when it drops, they take off at full intensity looking for the fastest way around the track. With multiple riders racing at once, the races are short but packed with excitement with explosive speed, jostling for position, and the question of whether to roll, double, or even triple that next jump.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-747x420.jpg 747w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-1068x601.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/bell-helmets-news-bob-haro-born-from-bmx-pic1-1400x787-copy-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a></p><p>After establishing the BMX Federation in 1981, the first World Championships was held the following year before BMX was fully integrated into the Union Cycliste Internationale (UCI) in 1993. BMX made its Olympic debut at the Beijing 2008 Games and has been part of the Olympic program ever since. 2021 is the first time that BMX Freestyle will be showcased in the Olympic games.</p><h2>Tokyo Olympics 2021 BMX Track</h2><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/T51G1LdTQiE?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>All the BMX race action will take place at the Ariake Urban Sports Park, close to the waterfront and near the Athletes Village in Ariake, Koto-Ku, Tokyo.</p><h2>Hows do the races work?</h2><p>Imagine — a max of eight riders at a time, all gated atop an 8m high 35-degree start hill, held back by a timed gate, waiting for it to beep and to sprint for the holeshot (<a href=\"https://youtu.be/VUjtaL-tfMc\">sometimes reaching over 2600 watts!</a>). Racers sprint for a clean look at the 400m long track with berms, jumps, rollers, and flat open sections. Riders race in full-face helmets, chest protection, long sleeves, and goggles, as the wrecks can be pretty dicey at the speed they can produce.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire.jpg\" alt=\"michelin pilot sx bmx racing tires\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/22100856/michelin-pilot-sx-bmx-race-tire-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>If you’re the first rider out of the gate — you have a distinct advantage and a clear look at the track, though it’s hard to keep that lead and stay on your line with others trying to take it. The short race involves explosive power and cunning race tactics as each corner allows another rider to overtake and throw the previous off their line — this sometimes leads to crashes, but as they say, “rubbing is racing.” The finish is an all-out sprint, and in the Olympics — every spot counts, so these will be extra exciting from the first heat to the last.</p><p>The Riders’ race rankings are based on time and points. There are 24 competitors in the men’s and women’s events — Six riders compete in each of the four heats over three rounds, with the top 16 proceedings to the semi-final, the top eight competing in the final medal rounds.</p><figure id=\"attachment_265666\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-265666\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics-.jpeg\" alt=\"Rio Team USA BMX Racing Olympics\" width=\"1280\" height=\"676\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--297x157.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--800x423.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--120x63.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--768x406.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--696x368.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--1068x564.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--795x420.jpeg 795w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics-.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--297x157.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--800x423.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--120x63.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--768x406.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--696x368.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--1068x564.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17122439/Rio-Team-USA-BMX-Racing-Olympics--795x420.jpeg 795w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-265666\">Photo credit: USA BMX</figcaption></figure><p>Though Team USA has been dominant, the Europeans, Australians, and Colombians are ready to take the gold this year. Connor Fields from the USA (who won gold at the Rio 2016 Games) will hope to continue his winning streak. It’s not that easy, though — Niek Kimmann and Twan Van Gendt from the Netherlands are looking good. Plus, Joris Daudet of France and Carlos Ramírez of Colombia are hoping to grab a medal — gold.</p><p>On the women’s side, Colombia’s Mariana Pajón is poised to take her third consecutive Olympic Games gold medal after her success at both London 2012 and Rio 2016. Top-ranked Alise Willoughby of the USA, 2018 World Champion Laura Smulders from the Netherlands, and Australia’s Saya Sakakibara all stand in the way as fierce competitors though — it will be an exciting watch.</p><figure id=\"attachment_265668\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-265668\"><a 